1. Overview of StarlingX
1.1 What is StarlingX?
StarlingX is a fully integrated edge cloud software stack that provides everything you need to deploy edge clouds from 1 to 100 servers.

출처: https://docs.starlingx.io/introduction/index-intro-27197f27ad41.html

Main features:

Operating system, storage, networking components, and cloud infrastructure in a single package for easy installation
Software optimized for edge application requirements
Pre-defined configurations to meet different edge cloud deployment needs
Tested and released as a complete stack to ensure compatibility between open source components
Built-in fault management and service management capabilities to provide high availability (HA) of user applications
Optimized for security, ultra-low latency, ultra-high service uptime, and streamlined operations
1.2 StarlingX Definition
출처: https://docs.starlingx.io/introduction/terms.html

StarlingX is an open-source, fully cloud infrastructure software stack for the edge used by the most demanding applications in industrial IoT, telecommunications, and other use cases. Through Kubernetes-based container orchestration and platform management layers, it provides a robust and flexible environment for all types of workloads, including containerization and bare metal.

