2.4 Kubernetes와 k3s 비교
Here's a comparison of the Kubernetes stack included in StarlingX (standard K8s + platform bundle) with the lightweight distribution k3s. k3s is designed for a single binary and minimal dependencies, and does not include many of the features provided by StarlingX out of the box.

Feature Comparison Table
Orchestration	표준 Kubernetes (1.29~1.32 멀티 버전)	Lightweight Kubernetes (single version, single binary)
Container Runtime	Native Docker Runtime	Default containerd (Docker is optional)
Primary CNI	Calico	Basic Flannel (Calico installed separately)
Additional Networking	Multus + SR-IOV CNI (가속 네트워킹)	No built-in supply, configure your own when needed
Storage (PVC)	Ceph-based (Rook-Ceph) required, StorageClass auto-generated	기본 local-path-provisioner, Ceph/Rook은 별도 설치
Local registry	로컬 Docker Registry 포함	Registry configurable, not platform default bundle
Package/Deployment	Helm + FluxCD (included on the platform)	Helm available, FluxCD is installed separately
Service Messages	Istio (Kiali 포함) 번들	None, install separately if required
Virtualization	KubeVirt Bundle	None, install separately if required
Certificates	cert-manager 번들	None, install separately if required
Ingress	nginx-ingress 번들	Traefik Basic or Separate Installation
Metrics	Metrics Server (플랫폼 포함)	Can be installed separately
Platform Integration	System Setup, Node Management, HA· FM, Integrated with Distributed Cloud	Standalone, no platform integrations like above
Summary of features that are not (or other) in K3S
Runtime: StarlingX specifies Docker as the default runtime. k3s is containerd default.
Networking: Integration settings with Calico, Multus, SR-IOV CNI, and platforms are not in the k3s default.
Storage: Rook-Ceph/Ceph-based PVC and platform-managed storage configurations are not present in the k3s base.
Platform bundles: Istio, FluxCD, KubeVirt, cert-manager, nginx-ingress, and Metrics Server are included in the platform on StarlingX, and k3s are all for additional installation and operation.
Platform integration: System settings (DNS/NTP/PTP, OAM, collectd, GNSS/SyncE, stalld, etc.), node management (CPU isolation, Hugepage, SR-IOV, Worker profiles, BMC, Power Manager), fault management (FM), high availability (HA), and integration with distributed clouds are not available on k3s alone.
