3.6 Distributed Cloud
출처: https://docs.starlingx.io/dist_cloud/kubernetes/overview-of-distributed-cloud.html, https://docs.starlingx.io/dist_cloud/kubernetes/distributed-cloud-architecture.html

The StarlingX Distributed Cloud configuration supports edge computing solutions by providing central management and orchestration of the geographically distributed StarlingX system network.

Core Design Principles:

Deploy Network Function Cloudification (NFC) Worker resources locally for maximum responsiveness — NFC refers to the transition of network functions to a cloud-native environment, including telecom workloads such as 5G vRAN (vDU, vCU), and UPF. The computing resources of the worker nodes running these NFC workloads are placed locally at the edge (subcloud) to minimize network latency.
Efficient management by concentrating management and control functions on the Central Cloud
Support for a scalable number of StarlingX edge systems synchronized in a central region over L3 networks
Each edge system scales from a single Simple to a Full Standard configuration with storage nodes
