9. Main Network Types
출처: https://docs.starlingx.io/introduction/terms.html

Management Network	Internal StarlingX infrastructure management monitoring and control. Also used for Ceph storage cluster access. Typically 10GE, external private	All nodes required
OAM Network	모든 외부 StarlingX 플랫폼 API 노출 (REST API, Horizon, SSH, SNMP). 일반적으로 1GE	Controller만 필수
PXEBoot Network	IPv4 network where nodes boot from the Controller	All nodes
Data Network(s)	pci-passthrough/sriov interface, used in hosted containers/VMs	Worker / All-in-One만
IPMI Network	An optional network to which the IPMI interfaces of all nodes connect	Optional
9.1 Management Network
Roles
Control, state synchronization, and monitoring traffic between Controller–Worker–Storage
Ceph (Rook-Ceph) storage cluster communication
K8s control plane (API Server, etc.), communication between services within the platform
Features: Interior only, no external exposure, typically constructed with 10GE. IPsec (strongSwan + XFRM) can be applied to this section to transparently encrypt traffic between nodes.
Connection: All nodes must be connected to this network.
9.2 OAM Network (Operations, Administration and Maintenance)
Roles
Externally accessible platform APIs only
REST APIs, web dashboards (Horizon), SSH, SNMP, etc. are served by the IP of this network
Features: More like "the only managed network with external exposure", usually 1GE. Certificates are issued and renewed with cert-manager and protected by TLS (HTTPS).
Connection: Controller only required. OAM IP can be set to Floating / Controller-0·1 / Gateway, etc. (IPv4/IPv6 dual-stack supported).
9.3 PXEBoot Network (PXE 부팅 네트워크)
Roles
The section where the node boots into the network (PXE) to the image provided by the Controller without disk
IPv4-only network used for installation and provisioning
Features: Traditional PXE structure to receive IP/boot information via DHCP, bootloader/kernel/initrd via TFTP.
Connection: All nodes must be connected to this network and able to boot PXE upon installation/reinstallation.
9.4 Data Network(s) (Data Network)
Roles
Application traffic only (5G vDU Fronthaul, VM/container data plane, etc.)
L2-based network decoupled from management traffic (Management/OAM)
Features
pci-passthrough: Assign a physical NIC directly to a specific container/VM
pci-sriov: Splitting a NIC into multiple VFs to share multiple workloads with high performance
data(vSwitch): Through the software bridge, normal traffic
Connection: Worker / All-in-One only. Not used in Controller-only configurations.
9.5 IPMI Network
Roles
Out-of-band management dedicated to server BMC (Baseboard Management Controller)
Power on/off, console, hardware monitoring, etc.
Feature: Optional. It is common to separate it into a separate L2.
Connectivity: IPMI ports on all nodes can be tied to this network.
